          "legendFormat": "{{service}}",
          "refId": "A"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": 32,
      "title": "Container Memory Limit by Service",
      "description": "The configured 'deploy.resources.limits.memory' per container, as cAdvisor sees it. As of 2026-07-21 every service has an explicit limit (kestra-webserver 1408M, kestra-executor 896M, kestra-scheduler 1024M, kestra-worker 768M, postgres/grafana/prometheus 512M each, cadvisor 256M, traefik 128M, node-exporter 64M) -- expect flat lines at those values. If any line reads 0 or doesn't match docker-compose.yml, that container didn't pick up its limit on last recreate and needs a `docker compose up -d` for that service.",
